SIMPLE: honeycomb
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Honeycomb
<hw>Hon"ey*comb`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>hunigcamb</ets>. See <er>Honey</er>, and 1st <er>Comb</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A mass of hexagonal waxen cells, formed by bees, and
used by them to hold their honey and their eggs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any substance, as a casting of iron, a piece of
worm-eaten wood, or of triple, etc., perforated with cells like a
honeycomb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Honeycomb moth</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the wax
moth.</cd> -- <col><b>Honeycomb stomach</b></col>. <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<cd>See <er>Reticulum</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honeycombed</ent>⟦br⟧
